  "prompt": "How do you jump to a certain page of a PDF file on the iPhone?",
  "response": "To jump to a specific page in a PDF file on an iPhone, you can use different methods depending on the app you're using:\n\n1. In Apple Books (default PDF viewer):\n- Open the PDF\n- Tap the screen to show navigation options\n- Tap the page number at the bottom of the screen\n- Enter the page number you want to view\n- Press \"Go\"\n\n2. In Adobe Acrobat Reader:\n- Open the PDF\n- Tap the page thumbnail icon (usually looks like stacked rectangles)\n- Scroll through thumbnails\n- Tap the page you want to view\n\n3. In Preview (if viewing via Mail or Files app):\n- Tap the page number at the bottom of the screen\n- Enter the desired page number\n- Press \"Go\"\n\n4. General scrolling method:\n- Most PDF apps allow you to scroll quickly by using the scroll bar or sliding your finger quickly along the right side of the screen\n\nThe exact method might vary slightly depending on your specific PDF app, but these are the most common ways to jump to a specific page on an iPhone.",
